1
00:00:24,810 --> 00:00:26,640
Bjorling...

2
00:00:27,310 --> 00:00:28,970
Suliotis?

3
00:00:29,640 --> 00:00:31,810
Almost. Bjorling is easy.

4
00:00:38,990 --> 00:00:40,650
Tebaldi?

5
00:00:40,720 --> 00:00:42,990
Bingo!

6
00:00:43,060 --> 00:00:45,220
It's my turn now.

7
00:00:50,070 --> 00:00:52,630
- Don't look!
- But I'm not looking.

8
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:54,190
Did Daddy look?

9
00:00:54,870 --> 00:00:56,360
Is that true?

10
00:01:09,290 --> 00:01:10,950
Oh, God!

11
00:01:12,730 --> 00:01:14,390
Gigli!

12
00:01:14,460 --> 00:01:17,400
That's obvious!
But what's the piece?

13
00:01:30,550 --> 00:01:31,880
Never heard it!

14
00:01:31,950 --> 00:01:33,610
Is it new?

15
00:01:34,450 --> 00:01:36,110
Seems to be.

16
00:01:37,290 --> 00:01:38,950
Well, darling?

17
00:01:47,130 --> 00:01:49,070
I'd say Handel.

18
00:01:49,130 --> 00:01:51,500
Right. But what is it?

19
00:01:54,170 --> 00:01:56,000
No idea!

20
00:02:02,550 --> 00:02:03,540
Well?

21
00:02:03,620 --> 00:02:05,950
I give up. What is it?

22
00:02:06,020 --> 00:02:07,820
Three-two to me!

23
00:02:10,830 --> 00:02:13,060
So, what is it?

24
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:15,390
Now get your hands off!

25
00:02:15,460 --> 00:02:17,400
Just listen!

26
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)

27
00:03:44,330 --> 00:03:46,160
That's cheating!

28
00:03:46,230 --> 00:03:47,220
Sorry?

29
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:49,290
It's cheating to be practicing.

30
00:03:49,370 --> 00:03:52,530
We've booked for 10:00
tomorrow morning. You are coming?

31
00:03:53,710 --> 00:03:54,940
Yes, sure.

32
00:04:00,350 --> 00:04:01,940
We'll put the boat in the water first.

33
00:04:02,620 --> 00:04:05,950
Can you give us a hand?
Let's say, in 20 minutes?

34
00:04:09,790 --> 00:04:12,230
Sure! Yes, I'll be there in 20 minutes.

35
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:14,130
Okay. Thanks.

36
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,690
See you in a tick.

37
00:04:24,980 --> 00:04:26,810
What's up with him?

38
00:04:26,880 --> 00:04:28,040
No idea.

39
00:04:28,110 --> 00:04:29,600
He seems in a huff.

40
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:31,840
She didn't say a word.

41
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:34,080
Who did you arrange
to play with tomorrow?

42
00:04:34,150 --> 00:04:35,490
Her.

43
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:36,920
Yesterday?

44
00:04:36,990 --> 00:04:38,650
The day before.

45
00:04:38,730 --> 00:04:39,660
Well?

46
00:04:40,490 --> 00:04:42,160
Nothing. She was totally normal.

47
00:04:42,230 --> 00:04:44,560
Sissi isn't there.

48
00:04:44,630 --> 00:04:47,620
Maybe she was just in the house.
Or at the beach.

49
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:51,470
Who were the two laddies?

50
00:04:52,140 --> 00:04:53,300
How should I know?

51
00:04:53,380 --> 00:04:57,310
They're probably relatives.
I think his brother has a son that age.

52
00:05:33,820 --> 00:05:36,810
Don't put that there!
Take your things upstairs!

53
00:05:36,890 --> 00:05:37,880
Okay.

54
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:39,290
Do it now!

55
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:42,190
Don't leave things in the entrance,
or someone will trip over.

56
00:05:42,260 --> 00:05:45,760
There's still so much left in the car.

57
00:05:45,830 --> 00:05:47,830
Are you listening?

58
00:05:47,900 --> 00:05:49,770
I'm going!

59
00:05:50,270 --> 00:05:53,270
Open the windows, will you.
We need to let some air in.

60
00:05:53,340 --> 00:05:55,280
Okay, Mom!

61
00:06:02,290 --> 00:06:04,880
Stop it, Rolfi! Stop it!

62
00:06:04,960 --> 00:06:06,790
Go on, get down!

63
00:06:06,860 --> 00:06:08,720
I have to unpack!

64
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:11,830
Go on, get out!

65
00:06:13,830 --> 00:06:15,800
- Georg?
- Yes?

66
00:06:15,870 --> 00:06:17,730
Where's the other box
with the food?

67
00:06:18,910 --> 00:06:20,240
I'll bring it right away.

68
00:06:20,310 --> 00:06:23,330
The golf gear was in the way.
I put it in the Rover last.

69
00:06:24,710 --> 00:06:29,450
We'd better get them in quick!
The things have got really hot!

70
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:32,510
This cool-box is totally useless.

71
00:06:32,590 --> 00:06:35,750
Stop it now, you'll knock me over.

72
00:06:35,830 --> 00:06:37,550
- The butter's all soft.
- Go see your mistress.

73
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:40,890
There're some cold cuts in the other box.

74
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:43,090
I'll get it. I'll just open the windows.

75
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:48,600
Leave the shutters closed on the lake side,
or it'll be too hot.

76
00:06:48,670 --> 00:06:50,390
Stop that. You'll get something

77
00:06:50,390 --> 00:06:52,670
in a minute, I must just put this away.

78
00:06:52,740 --> 00:06:56,910
Can't you call the dog?
He won't let me put the things away.

79
00:06:57,010 --> 00:06:58,410
Rolfi!

80
00:06:58,450 --> 00:06:59,510
Come here!

81
00:06:59,590 --> 00:07:00,750
Come and see your master!

82
00:07:00,820 --> 00:07:04,650
And the bottles too,
otherwise it'll all be warm by the evening.

83
00:07:08,330 --> 00:07:09,990
Stop it, Rolfi!

84
00:07:10,060 --> 00:07:11,550
Be quiet!

85
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:13,790
Come in!

86
00:07:14,700 --> 00:07:16,800
Sorry. He's off his head.

87
00:07:16,870 --> 00:07:18,360
Come in!

88
00:07:19,370 --> 00:07:20,640
Hello.

89
00:07:20,710 --> 00:07:23,540
Thanks for coming.
It'd have been tough on our own.

90
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:26,450
- No problem! This is...
- Paul. Nice to meet you.

91
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:28,250
Paul is son of a business colleague.

92
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:31,650
- It's a pleasure. Nice of you to help.
- Mine too.

93
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,380
I mean, the pleasure's mine.

94
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:37,620
- Not so much his.
- Will you be quiet?

95
00:07:37,690 --> 00:07:38,850
Lunatic!

96
00:07:38,930 --> 00:07:41,400
- Get into the house, go on!
- Come here, Rolfi!

97
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:44,700
- When did you get out here?
- Last week.

98
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:46,030
You too?

99
00:07:46,100 --> 00:07:47,540
- Yes.
- No.

100
00:07:47,610 --> 00:07:50,340
They didn't arrive till the weekend.
We came on Friday.

101
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:53,510
Hello, Fred!

102
00:07:53,580 --> 00:07:55,670
Nice of you to come over right away.

103
00:07:57,680 --> 00:08:00,180
- How's Eva?
- Fine.

104
00:08:01,050 --> 00:08:02,720
- Hello.
- Hello, madam.

105
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:05,250
...and where's Tropea?

106
00:08:05,330 --> 00:08:07,390
In south Italy. Right at the tip,

107
00:08:07,460 --> 00:08:10,450
- almost on the toes of the boot.
- But it's even hotter there.

108
00:08:10,530 --> 00:08:12,190
Not necessarily.

109
00:08:12,270 --> 00:08:14,580
Last year when I was in Italy it was freezing

110
00:08:14,580 --> 00:08:16,430
and here you were swimming, right?

111
00:08:16,510 --> 00:08:20,310
But it's a shame Sissi isn't here.
Without her, it's...

112
00:08:20,980 --> 00:08:22,710
- Be careful!
- I am!

113
00:08:22,780 --> 00:08:25,110
Careful, or the overhauling
will have been for nothing.

114
00:08:25,180 --> 00:08:27,170
Look, you can't see anything!

115
00:08:27,250 --> 00:08:28,240
Good.

116
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:31,280
Can you help me lift the boom over?

117
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:36,650
Mind the halyard!

118
00:08:51,010 --> 00:08:54,000
But she said she'd be there
for the whole holiday.

119
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:58,250
Listen, my boy.
I don't know why she isn't there either.

120
00:08:58,350 --> 00:09:01,850
Maybe she went to Tropea
with a school friend. I don't know.

121
00:09:01,890 --> 00:09:05,220
Tomorrow we'll go over and ask
her mother. She's bound to explain all.

122
00:09:05,290 --> 00:09:06,950
Now stop moping...

123
00:09:07,030 --> 00:09:09,190
Why was Uncle Fred so strange?

124
00:09:09,270 --> 00:09:11,430
I'm not surprised!

125
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:14,090
She got pretty worked up
about it last time.

126
00:09:14,770 --> 00:09:16,470
Forget it, please.

127
00:09:17,710 --> 00:09:20,400
She won't change,
and you'll just get in a state.

128
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:22,510
Exactly!

129
00:09:23,180 --> 00:09:24,880
That's it!

130
00:09:26,380 --> 00:09:28,880
Great. They're outside
working on the boat.

131
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:32,650
What?

132
00:09:33,790 --> 00:09:36,630
5:00 or 5:30.
I don't know the time here,

133
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:38,530
I mean, the kitchen clock has stopped.

134
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:40,790
I must get a new battery on Monday.

135
00:09:42,740 --> 00:09:44,070
What?

136
00:09:44,140 --> 00:09:45,900
Yes, that's what I'm doing now.

137
00:09:46,640 --> 00:09:48,370
Some fillets.

138
00:09:49,210 --> 00:09:51,270
Yes, you know, it's crazy. The whole thing

139
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:53,040
defrosted and now it needs eating.

140
00:09:53,950 --> 00:09:55,940
Come out and see us!

141
00:09:56,020 --> 00:10:00,010
No, really, like a fool, I froze
three pounds of beef fillet at once,

142
00:10:00,090 --> 00:10:02,250
and now here I am.

143
00:10:02,330 --> 00:10:05,890
No, I'm not joking.
Come and spend the weekend.

144
00:10:06,730 --> 00:10:07,660
What?

145
00:10:07,730 --> 00:10:10,200
He shouldn't make such a fuss.
Hold on.

146
00:10:10,870 --> 00:10:13,030
We need a sharp knife.

147
00:10:16,570 --> 00:10:18,630
I'd like to see it again some day.
Tell Dad.

148
00:10:18,710 --> 00:10:20,040
Sorry.

149
00:10:20,110 --> 00:10:22,600
Tell your beloved to pack up his laptop,

150
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:25,840
get in the car, and you'll be here
in two hours at the most!

151
00:10:27,790 --> 00:10:29,650
He shouldn't be so elusive.

152
00:10:31,260 --> 00:10:32,920
Okay. Think about it.

153
00:10:32,990 --> 00:10:35,390
In any case,
there's enough steak here for a week.

154
00:10:37,430 --> 00:10:38,590
Bye, Fanny.

155
00:10:38,670 --> 00:10:40,830
Say, give us another ring anyway

156
00:10:40,900 --> 00:10:43,500
to tell us whether we can expect you.

157
00:10:43,570 --> 00:10:45,060
Yes, bye.

158
00:10:45,140 --> 00:10:47,440
- What is it now?
- Someone's here.

159
00:10:47,510 --> 00:10:49,440
- Where?
- At the door.

160
00:10:54,020 --> 00:10:54,950
Hello?

161
00:10:55,020 --> 00:10:57,150
Hello. Sorry to disturb you.

162
00:10:57,250 --> 00:10:58,740
I'm from next door.

163
00:10:58,790 --> 00:11:01,720
We saw each other
when you stopped the car at the gate.

164
00:11:01,790 --> 00:11:03,450
Oh, yes, we did.

165
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:06,260
Come in, please.

166
00:11:07,430 --> 00:11:10,090
Hurry up, we're eating in 10 minutes!

167
00:11:10,170 --> 00:11:11,660
So what is it?

168
00:11:11,740 --> 00:11:13,230
Well...

169
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:14,970
Eva sent...

170
00:11:15,040 --> 00:11:17,030
I mean, Mrs. Berlinger sent me.

171
00:11:17,110 --> 00:11:18,600
She's just cooking...

172
00:11:19,350 --> 00:11:23,650
and she's run out of eggs.
She wonders if you can help her out.

173
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:25,480
But of course.

174
00:11:25,550 --> 00:11:27,280
- How many does she need?
- Four.

175
00:11:28,020 --> 00:11:29,010
Four?

176
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:32,020
- What for?
- Sorry?

177
00:11:32,090 --> 00:11:33,580
What for?

178
00:11:33,660 --> 00:11:35,650
What does she need the eggs for?

179
00:11:35,730 --> 00:11:37,390
I mean, what's she making?

180
00:11:37,470 --> 00:11:39,460
No idea.

181
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:42,360
Are they okay like that
or shall I wrap them?

182
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:44,530
As you like.

183
00:11:45,210 --> 00:11:47,040
So how did you get in?

184
00:11:47,110 --> 00:11:49,600
At the front.
I mean, by the beach.

185
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:51,840
But you didn't get wet at all!

186
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:53,410
There's a hole in the fence,

187
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:54,970
by the water, not in the water.

188
00:11:55,050 --> 00:11:56,250
Fred knows -

189
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:59,590
I mean, Mr. Berlinger knows it.
He showed me it.

190
00:11:59,690 --> 00:12:01,020
I see. Okay.

191
00:12:01,060 --> 00:12:02,720
So, wrapped, or is this okay?

192
00:12:02,790 --> 00:12:04,730
No, no, that's fine, no problem.

193
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:06,760
- Many thanks.
- You're welcome.

194
00:12:09,670 --> 00:12:12,160
Love to Eva.
Look forward to the golf tomorrow!

195
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:14,100
I'll tell her. Thanks again.

196
00:12:14,170 --> 00:12:16,660
And thanks again to Fred
and your friend -

197
00:12:16,740 --> 00:12:19,230
- Damn it!
- What's up?

198
00:12:25,390 --> 00:12:26,880
It's not a disaster.

199
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:28,620
Hang on.

200
00:12:42,910 --> 00:12:44,970
Thank God, we just arrived...

201
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:48,300
and I must shop
in the village on Monday.

202
00:12:48,380 --> 00:12:49,940
I'm really embarrassed.

203
00:12:50,010 --> 00:12:53,510
It's nothing. No one here eats eggs
for breakfast anyway,

204
00:12:53,580 --> 00:12:55,580
so it's not a major problem.

205
00:12:55,650 --> 00:12:57,590
That's a relief, thank you.

206
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:01,250
I should just have been more careful.

207
00:13:02,230 --> 00:13:05,930
- I put my left hand -
- Well, no point in crying over spilt milk.

208
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,330
You're really kind.

209
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:09,160
One does one's best.

210
00:13:17,140 --> 00:13:18,630
I'm really sorry.

211
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:24,580
I'm very clumsy, you know.

212
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:28,360
I think I've got two left hands.

213
00:13:28,420 --> 00:13:30,760
So you're ideal for carrying eggs.

214
00:13:30,830 --> 00:13:32,760
Yes, you could say.

215
00:13:34,260 --> 00:13:36,030
Well...

216
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:38,570
And what are we going to do now?

217
00:13:42,570 --> 00:13:46,240
We do have steak,
but we might be getting visitors,

218
00:13:46,310 --> 00:13:48,750
and they're bound to want eggs
for breakfast.

219
00:13:49,580 --> 00:13:51,780
But you'll have four left.

220
00:13:54,290 --> 00:13:57,280
After all, I did see
you had a box of twelve, right?

221
00:13:58,430 --> 00:14:00,760
You're right.

222
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:16,540
Shouldn't I wrap them up?

223
00:14:16,610 --> 00:14:18,270
No need.

224
00:14:18,350 --> 00:14:19,510
Are you sure?

225
00:14:19,580 --> 00:14:21,410
If you want to.

226
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:23,150
If I want to?

227
00:14:23,220 --> 00:14:25,280
Well, maybe it is better after all.

228
00:14:28,260 --> 00:14:30,590
- Oh, no!
- What's the matter?

229
00:14:32,760 --> 00:14:34,420
Oh, no!

230
00:15:06,700 --> 00:15:08,190
I'm sorry.

231
00:15:09,710 --> 00:15:12,170
Before you destroy the rest of the kitchen,

232
00:15:12,180 --> 00:15:14,700
maybe you should take your eggs and leave.

233
00:15:16,550 --> 00:15:18,040
Well...

234
00:15:22,050 --> 00:15:23,880
Here you are.

235
00:15:23,950 --> 00:15:25,550
Won't you wrap them?

236
00:15:42,410 --> 00:15:44,670
I'm really sorry.

237
00:15:45,510 --> 00:15:47,000
Honestly.

238
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:48,570
Me too.

239
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:56,550
There.

240
00:15:56,620 --> 00:15:59,290
- Here you are.
- Many thanks. Thank you.

241
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,330
I'll tell Mrs. Berlinger how nice you were.

242
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:03,460
Okay. Do as you see fit.

243
00:16:03,530 --> 00:16:05,690
- Bye.
- Good-bye.

244
00:17:09,540 --> 00:17:11,200
Excuse me?

245
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:23,050
Stop it! Rolfi!

246
00:17:23,120 --> 00:17:24,610
Excuse me!

247
00:17:26,390 --> 00:17:28,360
Off you go!

248
00:17:28,430 --> 00:17:30,090
Get lost!

249
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:32,000
I mean now!

250
00:17:35,070 --> 00:17:37,940
I'm sorry. He's completely harmless.

251
00:17:38,010 --> 00:17:40,500
- He just wants to have a game.
- Funny game.

252
00:17:41,180 --> 00:17:42,840
Did he hurt you?

253
00:17:42,910 --> 00:17:44,570
Peter's just afraid of dogs.

254
00:17:44,650 --> 00:17:46,840
- I'm sorry.
- Me too.

255
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:48,910
He jumped up on me.

256
00:17:48,990 --> 00:17:50,650
I'm sorry about that.

257
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:52,380
Well.

258
00:17:52,460 --> 00:17:54,450
Shall I lock him in so you can leave?

259
00:17:54,530 --> 00:17:56,550
- No need.
- I can tell my husband to -

260
00:17:56,630 --> 00:17:58,620
There's really no need, thanks.

261
00:17:58,730 --> 00:18:01,390
It's my fault.
I quite forgot the dog.

262
00:18:01,430 --> 00:18:03,590
Otherwise, I'd have come to fetch the...

263
00:18:04,340 --> 00:18:06,000
Oh! What a wonderful kit!

264
00:18:06,070 --> 00:18:07,730
Gallaway, isn't it?

265
00:18:10,980 --> 00:18:12,640
It's fantastic.

266
00:18:12,710 --> 00:18:14,270
May I?

267
00:18:15,150 --> 00:18:17,510
We hardly stand a chance for tomorrow!

268
00:18:19,350 --> 00:18:21,150
Good clubs don't make good golfers.

269
00:18:21,820 --> 00:18:23,480
That's true, yes.

270
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:28,060
Would it be cheeky of me
to ask if I can try it just once?

271
00:18:29,060 --> 00:18:31,220
Right now, outside?

272
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:32,560
Please! Okay?

273
00:18:32,640 --> 00:18:34,630
From the lawn out to the lake, okay?

274
00:18:36,510 --> 00:18:38,340
- If it makes you happy. I -
- Thanks.

275
00:18:43,610 --> 00:18:45,100
Excuse me.

276
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:47,510
He loves golf!

277
00:18:47,590 --> 00:18:49,550
- We both do.
- Sorry?

278
00:18:49,620 --> 00:18:51,450
Both of us. We both love golf.

279
00:19:06,510 --> 00:19:07,870
Rolfi!

280
00:19:07,940 --> 00:19:09,530
Stop it!

281
00:19:09,610 --> 00:19:11,270
Rolfi!

282
00:19:11,350 --> 00:19:13,010
Be quiet now!

283
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:15,850
What's up?

284
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:18,750
I don't know,
probably it's too hot for him too.

285
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:39,430
I'll go and see.

286
00:19:53,130 --> 00:19:54,960
Brilliant!

287
00:19:55,030 --> 00:19:57,360
Like the difference
between day and night.

288
00:19:58,770 --> 00:20:00,260
Thanks very much.

289
00:20:00,330 --> 00:20:01,820
You're welcome.

290
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:05,440
Where's Tom?

291
00:20:05,510 --> 00:20:07,670
- Who?
- Did you give him the eggs?

292
00:20:07,740 --> 00:20:09,270
Sorry?

293
00:20:12,810 --> 00:20:14,750
The driver is absolutely top-class.

294
00:20:14,820 --> 00:20:16,150
You must try it.

295
00:20:16,220 --> 00:20:17,380
Listen, young man.

296
00:20:17,450 --> 00:20:21,510
I don't know what game you're playing,
but I'm not going to join in.

297
00:20:23,830 --> 00:20:25,320
Will you go now, please?

298
00:20:29,470 --> 00:20:30,960
What game?

299
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:33,670
Sorry, madam, but I don't understand

300
00:20:33,670 --> 00:20:35,300
why you're suddenly so unfriendly.

301
00:20:36,470 --> 00:20:40,140
Have Tom or I
done anything to annoy you?

302
00:20:40,210 --> 00:20:42,150
Please, would you leave?

303
00:20:43,750 --> 00:20:46,450
Did you behave badly while I was outside?

304
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:49,050
Was he cheeky?

305
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:51,990
- Did he say anything -
- That's enough.

306
00:20:53,790 --> 00:20:56,190
I asked you to leave, so...

307
00:20:56,260 --> 00:20:57,930
please go.

308
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,160
Okay.

309
00:21:01,100 --> 00:21:04,560
I don't understand what's upset you so,
but if you insist...

310
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:06,300
Fine.

311
00:21:08,280 --> 00:21:11,110
Give the eggs to Tom
and we won't bother you again.

312
00:21:11,180 --> 00:21:12,840
I'm sorry?

313
00:21:12,920 --> 00:21:15,410
Of course we'll be telling Eva and Fred.

314
00:21:15,490 --> 00:21:18,850
Honestly, I've never experienced
anything like it before.

315
00:21:19,520 --> 00:21:21,350
What about you, Tom?

316
00:21:25,530 --> 00:21:27,730
May we have the eggs now, please?

317
00:21:28,630 --> 00:21:30,970
I told you to leave!

318
00:21:31,040 --> 00:21:32,970
Did I do something wrong...

319
00:21:33,040 --> 00:21:35,030
Now just get out of here, you...

320
00:21:35,110 --> 00:21:37,100
Is the dog with you?
What's going on?

321
00:21:37,180 --> 00:21:39,340
- Get them out!
- Good to see you, Mr. Schober.

322
00:21:39,410 --> 00:21:40,900
You are Mr. Schober, right?

323
00:21:40,980 --> 00:21:42,970
Fred, I mean, Mr. Berlinger told me.

324
00:21:43,050 --> 00:21:45,350
What?
What's the matter?

325
00:21:45,420 --> 00:21:47,910
- Throw him out!
- Your wife's mistaken.

326
00:21:47,990 --> 00:21:49,650
I'm very glad you're here.

327
00:21:49,720 --> 00:21:51,890
I'm sure you can clarify
the misunderstanding.

328
00:21:51,960 --> 00:21:54,950
- Daddy, I can't -
- Please, Georg!

329
00:21:59,300 --> 00:22:01,900
It's outrageous!

330
00:22:02,910 --> 00:22:05,670
Can I explain how this
misunderstanding arose?

331
00:22:05,740 --> 00:22:08,910
Mrs. Berlinger sent me over
to fetch some eggs.

332
00:22:08,980 --> 00:22:10,470
So what? And then?

333
00:22:10,550 --> 00:22:13,880
Your wife gave the eggs to Peter,
but he smashed them.

334
00:22:13,950 --> 00:22:17,050
Yes. And she gave me
four more eggs, but...

335
00:22:17,120 --> 00:22:19,280
then the dog jumped up on me...

336
00:22:19,360 --> 00:22:20,850
and now...

337
00:22:20,930 --> 00:22:23,760
But it was a 12-pack,
and you're shopping Monday anyway...

338
00:22:23,830 --> 00:22:25,820
We just want the eggs,

339
00:22:25,900 --> 00:22:27,390
that's all.

340
00:22:28,070 --> 00:22:30,230
Can you tell me what's going on?

341
00:22:39,650 --> 00:22:41,140
Give them the eggs.

342
00:22:41,220 --> 00:22:43,380
Hold on!
Can you wait a moment?

343
00:22:43,450 --> 00:22:45,480
- Can I take them?
- Just a moment.

344
00:22:45,550 --> 00:22:47,220
What's going on?

345
00:22:47,290 --> 00:22:50,780
It can't just be about these ridiculous eggs.
Why this rage?

346
00:22:50,860 --> 00:22:53,350
I'm not justifying myself to these...

347
00:22:54,530 --> 00:22:58,160
I asked you to throw them out.
I must have my reasons.

348
00:23:00,500 --> 00:23:02,840
Do as you wish.
For me, the subject is closed.

349
00:23:02,910 --> 00:23:04,070
Anna?

350
00:23:08,450 --> 00:23:10,110
Would you please leave?

351
00:23:10,620 --> 00:23:12,780
My wife doesn't feel well.

352
00:23:15,450 --> 00:23:19,690
I can't act as arbitrator in a matter
I don't know anything about.

353
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:21,420
Please, would you leave?

354
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:29,930
What is it?

355
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:31,490
If you don't mind?

356
00:23:33,670 --> 00:23:35,640
So give them to him!

357
00:23:35,710 --> 00:23:37,370
What's going on?

358
00:23:37,450 --> 00:23:39,440
Nothing's going on.

359
00:23:39,510 --> 00:23:42,850
She gave him the eggs,
the dog jumped on him, he smashed them.

360
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:45,250
He wants more.
Is it so complicated?

361
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:47,150
What kind of tone is that supposed to be?

362
00:23:47,820 --> 00:23:49,490
Watch I don't smash your balls as well!

363
00:23:53,500 --> 00:23:56,160
Now get out! Right now!

364
00:24:00,770 --> 00:24:02,260
Is it broken?

365
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:07,780
Be good, now.

366
00:24:07,850 --> 00:24:09,340
Behave yourself!

367
00:24:12,450 --> 00:24:14,110
Be nice!

368
00:24:14,190 --> 00:24:16,180
I don't want to hurt you,
but behave yourself!

369
00:24:21,460 --> 00:24:23,400
Please stay where you are.

370
00:24:23,460 --> 00:24:24,950
Please stay there!

371
00:24:26,630 --> 00:24:29,330
- He hit me in the face.
- Yes. He started it.

372
00:24:31,170 --> 00:24:33,660
You can help him if you want,
but no messing about.

373
00:24:35,680 --> 00:24:37,840
- Bring him a chair.
- My knee!

374
00:24:37,910 --> 00:24:40,910
- He should take off his pants and sit down.
- A chair!

375
00:24:40,980 --> 00:24:43,480
Peter studies medicine. He'll fix it.

376
00:24:43,550 --> 00:24:45,720
Take off your pants, please.

377
00:24:56,030 --> 00:24:58,900
If you won't let me see your wound,
I can't help you.

378
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:01,240
Sorry I hurt you,

379
00:25:01,270 --> 00:25:04,210
but you left me no choice,
you must admit.

380
00:25:05,380 --> 00:25:08,610
Be reasonable, Mr. Schober.
Let him look at your leg.

381
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:10,510
He's sure to be able to help.

382
00:25:12,990 --> 00:25:14,650
Will you leave please?

383
00:25:14,720 --> 00:25:15,920
Please!

384
00:25:17,260 --> 00:25:18,920
This won't get us anywhere.

385
00:25:18,990 --> 00:25:21,830
You must let him help you.
You haven't any choice.

386
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:24,790
You're a ship's captain, sir.

387
00:25:25,570 --> 00:25:28,870
You know that on board ship,
the Captain's word is final.

388
00:25:29,540 --> 00:25:31,530
So, what do you want to do, sir?

389
00:25:32,380 --> 00:25:35,040
Do you want to call someone?
An ambulance?

390
00:25:35,110 --> 00:25:36,600
Or the police?

391
00:25:37,350 --> 00:25:40,680
Go on! I won't stop you.
Nor will Tom.

392
00:25:40,750 --> 00:25:42,480
That's a promise!

393
00:25:42,550 --> 00:25:43,210
Right?

394
00:25:48,530 --> 00:25:50,190
What are you waiting for?

395
00:25:57,540 --> 00:26:00,100
He dropped the mobile in the water.

396
00:26:10,150 --> 00:26:11,810
Why are you doing this?

397
00:26:11,890 --> 00:26:13,380
Why not?

398
00:26:14,660 --> 00:26:16,750
Okay, then, another game.

399
00:26:17,430 --> 00:26:19,400
A guessing game.

400
00:26:20,760 --> 00:26:22,420
What's this?

401
00:26:37,180 --> 00:26:38,510
A golf ball.

402
00:26:38,580 --> 00:26:41,110
Exactly, sir, a golf ball.

403
00:26:42,190 --> 00:26:44,350
And why do I have it here in my pocket?

404
00:26:47,430 --> 00:26:49,360
The lady knows.

405
00:26:49,430 --> 00:26:51,090
Because...

406
00:26:54,200 --> 00:26:55,860
Well?

407
00:26:59,170 --> 00:27:00,000
Well?

408
00:27:01,280 --> 00:27:03,440
- Because you didn't hit it.
- Exactly!

409
00:27:03,510 --> 00:27:05,670
And why didn't I hit it?

410
00:27:05,750 --> 00:27:07,150
Because you were stopped.

411
00:27:07,220 --> 00:27:08,210
Exactly.

412
00:27:08,950 --> 00:27:10,780
And because I had to test
the club another way.

413
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:25,030
Where is he?

414
00:27:25,100 --> 00:27:26,430
Cold.

415
00:27:28,340 --> 00:27:29,830
Cold.

416
00:27:30,580 --> 00:27:32,170
Colder.

417
00:27:34,680 --> 00:27:35,840
Cold.

418
00:27:53,270 --> 00:27:55,990
Warmer.

419
00:27:58,310 --> 00:28:00,470
Hotter.

420
00:28:00,540 --> 00:28:01,870
Cold.

421
00:28:22,940 --> 00:28:24,430
Really cold.

422
00:28:33,680 --> 00:28:35,840
Warmer, hotter, boiling!

423
00:29:00,040 --> 00:29:02,670
Would you kindly get me
some food from the kitchen?

424
00:29:03,850 --> 00:29:05,340
Would it be possible?

425
00:29:13,160 --> 00:29:15,650
Bananas or something like that.

426
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:21,490
And don't think of picking up
a knife or something.

427
00:29:21,570 --> 00:29:23,400
I'd be sorry if you did.

428
00:29:23,470 --> 00:29:24,960
For your sake.

429
00:29:35,980 --> 00:29:38,480
The sun's coming out again.

430
00:29:43,160 --> 00:29:45,680
Very kind of you. Thank you.

431
00:30:01,380 --> 00:30:03,040
Hello! Sweetie!

432
00:30:07,020 --> 00:30:08,950
Where are you?

433
00:30:11,220 --> 00:30:13,390
Come on down!

434
00:30:14,730 --> 00:30:17,560
We're both thinking the same, aren't we?

435
00:30:22,900 --> 00:30:24,960
We saw your boat!

436
00:30:25,610 --> 00:30:28,510
Hello, Gerda!
Hello, Robert!

437
00:30:28,580 --> 00:30:31,240
How long have you been here?

438
00:30:31,310 --> 00:30:32,800
Not long.

439
00:30:32,880 --> 00:30:35,820
We're still unpacking.

440
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:37,980
How long are you staying?

441
00:30:38,050 --> 00:30:39,890
A week or two.

442
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:41,620
We're not sure yet.

443
00:30:41,690 --> 00:30:43,020
Great!

444
00:30:43,090 --> 00:30:45,860
- Hello, darling, lovely to see you.
- Hello.

445
00:30:51,940 --> 00:30:53,600
Have you met my sister?

446
00:30:53,670 --> 00:30:56,110
No! Pleased to meet you!

447
00:30:56,170 --> 00:30:57,330
Hello, Robert!

448
00:30:57,440 --> 00:30:59,140
- Everything okay?
- Of course.

449
00:31:01,610 --> 00:31:05,020
This is Paul.
He's living with our neighbors.

450
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:07,420
- Hello, Paul!
- Hello, pleased to meet you!

451
00:31:07,490 --> 00:31:09,420
Are you cold?

452
00:31:09,490 --> 00:31:12,150
No, I have eczema.

453
00:31:12,230 --> 00:31:15,390
You should go swimming.
The water here does wonders for you.

454
00:31:15,460 --> 00:31:16,790
Thank you for the tip.

455
00:31:16,870 --> 00:31:18,230
Hello.

456
00:31:18,300 --> 00:31:19,270
How's Georg?

457
00:31:19,930 --> 00:31:21,490
Very well, thank you!

458
00:31:21,570 --> 00:31:23,060
So where is he?

459
00:31:23,140 --> 00:31:25,470
He pulled a muscle putting the mast up.

460
00:31:25,540 --> 00:31:27,030
So he's lying down.

461
00:31:27,110 --> 00:31:28,600
That's a real shame.

462
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:30,840
That's the result of doing
everything yourself.

463
00:31:30,910 --> 00:31:33,320
Robert wouldn't dream of putting our boat

464
00:31:33,320 --> 00:31:35,250
in the water on his own, right?

465
00:31:37,090 --> 00:31:39,450
Tell your beloved to pull
himself together.

466
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:42,520
We barbecue nearly every night.
We can't do without him.

467
00:31:42,590 --> 00:31:44,250
I'll tell him!

468
00:31:44,330 --> 00:31:47,660
I mean it. As soon as he's better,
come and see us right away.

469
00:31:47,730 --> 00:31:51,130
Robert's son is here with his girlfriend.
He'll like her.

470
00:31:51,970 --> 00:31:53,300
Right then.

471
00:31:54,610 --> 00:31:56,100
Have a good time, darling.

472
00:31:56,180 --> 00:31:58,510
If the wind doesn't change, bring the car.

473
00:31:58,610 --> 00:32:00,550
The weather forecast says wind.

474
00:32:00,580 --> 00:32:02,670
For tomorrow.

475
00:32:02,750 --> 00:32:05,410
- I said to Robert we'd get nowhere.
- Where are you moored?

476
00:32:05,490 --> 00:32:06,980
What?

477
00:32:07,050 --> 00:32:09,790
Oh! Over there,
behind the headland.

478
00:32:09,860 --> 00:32:11,020
But on the other side.

479
00:32:12,360 --> 00:32:15,190
- The wooden house covered in ivy?
- That's it.

480
00:32:15,260 --> 00:32:18,360
- It looks very pretty.
- Indeed it is, young man.

481
00:32:18,430 --> 00:32:20,270
Right then. Bye!

482
00:32:26,740 --> 00:32:29,300
- Are you staying all week?
- This week, sure.

483
00:32:33,490 --> 00:32:34,980
Might see you tonight!

484
00:32:35,050 --> 00:32:37,990
As you like.
We're always pleased to see you!

485
00:32:38,720 --> 00:32:40,390
I don't know yet.

486
00:32:40,460 --> 00:32:43,790
- We'll see how Georg is.
- Yes, you see! See you soon!

487
00:32:47,300 --> 00:32:49,960
They'll be here
in two hours at the latest...

488
00:32:50,040 --> 00:32:51,870
and then this farce will be over.

489
00:32:51,940 --> 00:32:53,770
Sorry, but that's not quite true.

490
00:32:53,840 --> 00:32:56,140
I heard the end of your phone call.

491
00:32:56,210 --> 00:33:00,150
You asked your friends to call you back
if they were coming tonight.

492
00:33:00,250 --> 00:33:01,740
Or did I misunderstand you?

493
00:33:01,780 --> 00:33:04,310
Even if they can't reach us,
they'll still come.

494
00:33:04,390 --> 00:33:06,010
Is lying allowed?

495
00:33:06,920 --> 00:33:08,410
Just a moment!

496
00:33:14,130 --> 00:33:15,620
There you are. Please.

497
00:33:16,970 --> 00:33:19,300
You really can speak to us openly.

498
00:33:19,370 --> 00:33:23,200
You'll feel much better.
We're also being very open with you.

499
00:33:27,880 --> 00:33:30,710
Perhaps try putting a cushion under it.

500
00:33:31,880 --> 00:33:34,910
If you'd accepted Peter's help,
it would be hurting less.

501
00:33:37,090 --> 00:33:39,250
I'm quite willing to help you.

502
00:33:39,330 --> 00:33:41,490
But I don't want to impose.

503
00:33:45,570 --> 00:33:47,190
Careful!

504
00:33:48,700 --> 00:33:51,730
Yes, raise the leg.
That's bound to be more comfortable.

505
00:33:55,410 --> 00:33:57,740
There we are! Done!

506
00:33:59,080 --> 00:34:00,910
Can you leave it out, you bastards?

507
00:34:02,620 --> 00:34:04,110
Is that an offer?

508
00:34:04,190 --> 00:34:05,680
- What?
- Using our first names?

509
00:34:11,530 --> 00:34:13,360
I'm very happy about that.

510
00:34:13,430 --> 00:34:16,370
It does vastly simplify our communication.

511
00:34:18,040 --> 00:34:20,700
I'd still like to apologize for just now,

512
00:34:20,770 --> 00:34:22,710
for being too familiar,

513
00:34:23,380 --> 00:34:25,560
but you must admit that the smack was

514
00:34:25,560 --> 00:34:27,870
an unreasonable reaction nonetheless.

515
00:34:30,750 --> 00:34:32,080
Paul.

516
00:34:35,890 --> 00:34:37,880
This is Peter.

517
00:34:39,430 --> 00:34:42,090
Come here, Tom.
Have you no manners?

518
00:34:42,160 --> 00:34:43,820
Give Georg your hand.

519
00:34:45,900 --> 00:34:47,560
Here, it's for the pain.

520
00:34:47,640 --> 00:34:50,160
What? To you, we're non-existent?

521
00:34:50,240 --> 00:34:52,570
- Being on familiar terms doesn't mean -
- You bastard...

522
00:35:09,530 --> 00:35:11,760
Quiet! Please!

523
00:35:11,830 --> 00:35:12,990
Stop!

524
00:35:15,170 --> 00:35:18,330
Stop it now, otherwise your mother
will get it, do you understand?

525
00:35:20,670 --> 00:35:21,660
Understand?

526
00:35:27,380 --> 00:35:29,040
Keep quiet now.

527
00:35:38,560 --> 00:35:41,220
What a scene,
just for being on first-name terms!

528
00:35:54,910 --> 00:35:57,280
We were only trying to improve relations.

529
00:35:58,180 --> 00:36:00,450
- I thought we could -
- Why are you doing that?

530
00:36:03,460 --> 00:36:05,120
Fatty, why are you doing that?

531
00:36:09,860 --> 00:36:11,350
Go on, tell us!

532
00:36:12,870 --> 00:36:15,930
I don't know. I...

533
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:17,490
The Captain wants to know.

534
00:36:17,570 --> 00:36:18,400
Why?

535
00:36:19,740 --> 00:36:21,040
Well?

536
00:36:25,210 --> 00:36:27,770
It's difficult to talk about it. I...

537
00:36:27,850 --> 00:36:29,340
Don't be shy.

538
00:36:31,090 --> 00:36:33,050
You know just how hard it is...

539
00:36:33,990 --> 00:36:36,420
My God, what a fuss!

540
00:36:37,090 --> 00:36:38,860
His father got a divorce...

541
00:36:38,930 --> 00:36:40,420
