778
00:59:25,880 --> 00:59:27,540
Please. Sure.

779
00:59:28,710 --> 00:59:31,880
You must wonder, Captain,
where this lovely rifle comes from.

780
00:59:33,380 --> 00:59:34,940
Or does it seem familiar?

781
00:59:35,450 --> 00:59:37,650
Haven't you ever been hunting with Fred?

782
00:59:39,830 --> 00:59:42,990
Do you know, your little darling
just tried to kill me with it?

783
00:59:46,000 --> 00:59:50,160
Scarcely believable, but it's the truth,
and nothing but the truth.

784
00:59:50,240 --> 00:59:51,730
Isn't that right, Georgie?

785
00:59:56,840 --> 00:59:58,510
What do you say, Tom?

786
00:59:58,580 --> 00:59:59,910
Dreadful.

787
01:00:01,850 --> 01:00:03,510
What's the time?

788
01:00:03,590 --> 01:00:06,250
Just after 11:00.

789
01:00:06,320 --> 01:00:09,290
We should start thinking about our bet,
don't you think?

790
01:00:11,460 --> 01:00:15,120
Actually we ought to be grateful
to Georgie for helping us.

791
01:00:15,800 --> 01:00:17,130
One for Beavis,

792
01:00:17,200 --> 01:00:18,960
one for Butt-Head.

793
01:00:22,740 --> 01:00:25,640
A, B, BOO and out go you!

794
01:00:25,710 --> 01:00:30,170
You're not leaving at this stage.
First you'll have to say your age.

795
01:00:32,920 --> 01:00:34,250
Well?

796
01:00:37,820 --> 01:00:39,450
She doesn't want to play.

797
01:00:39,960 --> 01:00:42,050
Well, how old do you think she is?

798
01:00:44,070 --> 01:00:45,560
37?

799
01:00:47,570 --> 01:00:49,300
No flab...

800
01:00:49,800 --> 01:00:51,500
So I'd say,

801
01:00:51,570 --> 01:00:54,060
let's be generous,
let's say 35.

802
01:00:56,380 --> 01:00:57,310
Agreed?

803
01:01:00,150 --> 01:01:01,480
She agrees.

804
01:01:01,550 --> 01:01:03,540
Who are you going to start counting with?

805
01:01:04,250 --> 01:01:05,190
Her?

806
01:01:09,660 --> 01:01:12,150
And now I'm going to
get myself something to eat.

807
01:01:13,830 --> 01:01:15,490
One, two, three,

808
01:01:15,570 --> 01:01:17,660
four, five, six, seven...

809
01:01:34,190 --> 01:01:36,120
Can I get anyone anything?

810
01:02:12,800 --> 01:02:14,730
You're an idiot, Fatty.

811
01:02:14,800 --> 01:02:16,240
You don't shoot the person you've

812
01:02:16,240 --> 01:02:18,170
counted out, but the one that's left over!

813
01:02:18,240 --> 01:02:19,570
What's wrong with you?

814
01:02:19,640 --> 01:02:21,800
- He tried to escape!
- So what?

815
01:02:21,870 --> 01:02:24,040
That's no reason
to get trigger-happy.

816
01:02:24,110 --> 01:02:25,600
Have you no sense of timing?

817
01:02:26,450 --> 01:02:27,940
What's the time?

818
01:02:28,020 --> 01:02:29,780
Just before 12:00.

819
01:02:29,850 --> 01:02:31,340
Shit.

820
01:02:31,420 --> 01:02:33,080
We'll get nothing from the others now.

821
01:02:34,260 --> 01:02:37,090
- Let's get out of here.
- Fine.

822
01:02:37,160 --> 01:02:41,120
Thanks so much for the driver.
I'll put it back in the bag, okay?

823
01:02:41,200 --> 01:02:42,190
Thanks.

824
01:02:43,330 --> 01:02:44,820
So, have a good evening!

825
01:02:44,900 --> 01:02:46,230
Good-bye!

826
01:02:46,300 --> 01:02:47,600
Bye!

827
01:05:11,700 --> 01:05:13,630
They've gone.

828
01:05:51,010 --> 01:05:53,670
Do you hear? They've gone!

829
01:06:37,230 --> 01:06:39,720
I'll get a knife.

830
01:08:28,720 --> 01:08:30,750
Come on.
Calm down now.

831
01:08:36,230 --> 01:08:38,560
Take deep breaths.

832
01:08:42,140 --> 01:08:43,630
Come on, darling.

833
01:08:44,910 --> 01:08:46,570
Calm down now.

834
01:08:49,250 --> 01:08:51,080
Calm yourself.

835
01:08:53,580 --> 01:08:54,920
Calm yourself.

836
01:08:54,990 --> 01:08:57,820
That's it. Take some deep breaths.

837
01:10:52,820 --> 01:10:55,150
We've got to get out of here.

838
01:10:56,990 --> 01:10:59,050
What if they come back?

839
01:11:01,730 --> 01:11:04,160
Do you think you can walk
if I support you?

840
01:11:09,100 --> 01:11:10,590
I'll try.

841
01:11:20,450 --> 01:11:22,780
What's wrong with your arm?

842
01:11:28,560 --> 01:11:32,620
Shall I try and make a splint for it?
Then I can hold you better.

843
01:11:34,300 --> 01:11:36,460
No, it's okay. Come on.

844
01:12:01,430 --> 01:12:02,920
Let's go.

845
01:12:10,010 --> 01:12:11,500
Let's go.

846
01:12:21,290 --> 01:12:22,780
Okay?

847
01:12:32,800 --> 01:12:34,460
No! Anna!

848
01:12:36,500 --> 01:12:37,870
No!

849
01:13:25,120 --> 01:13:26,790
They've locked the door.

850
01:13:27,760 --> 01:13:29,590
We must use the window.

851
01:13:29,660 --> 01:13:31,150
I can't.

852
01:13:31,230 --> 01:13:32,720
Georg!

853
01:13:32,800 --> 01:13:35,130
- Please!
- I can't manage it.

854
01:13:35,200 --> 01:13:36,360
You go.

855
01:13:36,440 --> 01:13:39,930
It's crazy wasting so much time.
Run for it. Please!

856
01:13:40,010 --> 01:13:41,840
Climb out of the kitchen window.

857
01:13:41,910 --> 01:13:44,070
Try to get as far as the inn, or...

858
01:13:44,150 --> 01:13:46,640
If we're locked in here,
the gate will be shut too.

859
01:13:48,320 --> 01:13:50,250
That's true.

860
01:13:51,090 --> 01:13:53,750
Take a pair of pliers and cut the fence.

861
01:13:53,820 --> 01:13:57,760
But careful on the road.
Maybe they're waiting out there.

862
01:13:59,260 --> 01:14:01,290
Where are the pliers?

863
01:14:03,970 --> 01:14:06,060
I don't know.

864
01:14:06,140 --> 01:14:08,130
Here, in the kitchen.

865
01:14:10,140 --> 01:14:11,630
No,

866
01:14:11,710 --> 01:14:13,240
down at the boat shed.

867
01:14:14,450 --> 01:14:16,440
I can't leave you alone here.

868
01:14:16,520 --> 01:14:18,010
Go now, please!

869
01:14:19,350 --> 01:14:21,510
Put some clothes on.

870
01:14:21,590 --> 01:14:24,080
And shoes too, so you can run.

871
01:14:29,760 --> 01:14:31,930
Hold on, the bag's still here.

872
01:14:32,000 --> 01:14:33,490
Down there.

873
01:14:46,120 --> 01:14:48,050
I'll hide down in the wine cellar.

874
01:14:48,720 --> 01:14:50,550
The key must be in the door.

875
01:14:52,490 --> 01:14:55,320
I'll shut myself in
and wait for you to come back.

876
01:15:00,330 --> 01:15:02,660
How will you get down there?

877
01:15:02,730 --> 01:15:04,220
I'll manage.

878
01:15:20,450 --> 01:15:22,390
Go now! Please!

879
01:15:43,150 --> 01:15:45,080
The mobile! It's working again!

880
01:15:45,150 --> 01:15:46,080
What?

881
01:15:46,150 --> 01:15:48,640
It's working!
It's obviously dried out.

882
01:15:48,720 --> 01:15:50,880
- So get on the phone!
- Who to?

883
01:15:50,960 --> 01:15:53,450
Anyone! The police!

884
01:15:53,530 --> 01:15:55,190
What's their number?

885
01:15:55,260 --> 01:15:56,920
No idea.

886
01:15:57,030 --> 01:15:58,390
Call my mother...

887
01:15:58,430 --> 01:16:00,400
Your father-
No, wait...

888
01:16:00,470 --> 01:16:03,130
Call Peter, he's at home,
I know, he wanted to -

889
01:16:03,200 --> 01:16:05,870
Press four and then hit speed-dial.

890
01:16:08,710 --> 01:16:10,200
It's not ringing.

891
01:16:12,710 --> 01:16:14,200
Let me listen.

892
01:16:17,390 --> 01:16:18,720
But there is a signal!

893
01:16:18,790 --> 01:16:20,950
Some of the contacts
are probably still damp.

894
01:16:39,980 --> 01:16:40,970
Nothing.

895
01:16:43,150 --> 01:16:45,810
Get the hair dryer.
Maybe it'll help.

896
01:16:46,650 --> 01:16:48,810
Can you pass me the chair?

897
01:17:15,620 --> 01:17:17,450
It won't work.

898
01:19:01,270 --> 01:19:02,760
Leave it, come on.

899
01:19:04,110 --> 01:19:06,010
Maybe it's permanently broken.

900
01:19:06,080 --> 01:19:07,570
Get going!

901
01:19:10,250 --> 01:19:13,740
We're wasting far too much time.
Let me do it.

902
01:19:16,090 --> 01:19:17,920
Go on!

903
01:19:20,430 --> 01:19:22,590
Pull me over there on the chair.

904
01:19:22,660 --> 01:19:25,150
I think it'll be easier than walking.

905
01:19:57,840 --> 01:19:59,030
Thanks.

906
01:20:00,500 --> 01:20:02,440
And now, run!

907
01:20:15,020 --> 01:20:16,990
Please, forgive me!

908
01:20:24,200 --> 01:20:25,790
It -

909
01:20:36,880 --> 01:20:38,870
I love you!

910
01:20:48,060 --> 01:20:49,550
Run, please!

911
01:22:45,720 --> 01:22:47,890
Help!

912
01:23:20,200 --> 01:23:22,690
Peter? It's Georg!

913
01:23:24,200 --> 01:23:27,140
Can you hear me?
I can barely hear you!

914
01:23:28,970 --> 01:23:31,640
Listen, if you can hear me,

915
01:23:31,710 --> 01:23:34,580
send the police over to our
lake house, right away!

916
01:23:36,310 --> 01:23:37,580
Hello?

917
01:23:38,080 --> 01:23:39,950
Shit!

918
01:23:51,730 --> 01:23:53,670
Peter! Can you hear me?

919
01:26:01,180 --> 01:26:02,340
Stop!

920
01:28:15,700 --> 01:28:17,190
Missed!

921
01:28:17,270 --> 01:28:18,760
Morning, Captain.

922
01:28:20,400 --> 01:28:21,890
Morning.

923
01:28:21,970 --> 01:28:24,800
They'll be there any minute.

924
01:28:24,870 --> 01:28:27,870
We'll have to hurry then.
Right, Beavis?

925
01:28:27,950 --> 01:28:29,780
Why don't you believe me?

926
01:28:29,850 --> 01:28:33,040
- How old did we say? 37?
- 35.

927
01:28:33,120 --> 01:28:37,180
Good that the battery
charger's in the car!

928
01:28:37,260 --> 01:28:39,690
- If it's her age, you must start with her.
- Why?

929
01:28:39,760 --> 01:28:41,590
- The battery was okay.
- That's the rules.

930
01:28:41,660 --> 01:28:43,490
Okay, I'll start with her.

931
01:28:43,560 --> 01:28:45,890
Yes, I know.

932
01:28:45,970 --> 01:28:49,900
It's time you had another idea.
The lady tried that trick before.

933
01:28:49,970 --> 01:28:51,460
Count faster, Beavis.

934
01:28:53,140 --> 01:28:55,230
Do you think we have no imagination?

935
01:28:55,310 --> 01:28:58,140
Without risk, you can't have a bet,
that's obvious, Captain.

936
01:28:58,250 --> 01:29:00,180
You must have a chance too.

937
01:29:00,210 --> 01:29:02,130
The wind blows where it wishes.

938
01:29:02,130 --> 01:29:04,910
That's the joy of sailing, don't you think?

939
01:29:04,990 --> 01:29:06,320
Right then!

940
01:29:06,390 --> 01:29:07,880
...thirty-four, thirty-five!

941
01:29:07,960 --> 01:29:10,120
Don't make the same mistake again.

942
01:29:10,190 --> 01:29:12,180
It's the one that's left who's turn it is,

943
01:29:12,180 --> 01:29:13,690
not the one who's counted out.

944
01:29:19,300 --> 01:29:20,240
Hang on.

945
01:29:20,300 --> 01:29:22,970
I can see a new toy.

946
01:29:23,710 --> 01:29:25,770
I assume we owe this to the lady?

947
01:29:27,950 --> 01:29:30,610
This will make things a bit more amusing.

948
01:29:32,280 --> 01:29:34,550
The dumb suffer in unspectacular fashion.

949
01:29:36,220 --> 01:29:38,050
We want to offer the audience something...

950
01:29:38,120 --> 01:29:40,180
and show what we can do, right?

951
01:29:49,400 --> 01:29:51,240
You can join in again now.

952
01:29:54,910 --> 01:29:57,400
We were already
on first-name terms, right?

953
01:29:58,910 --> 01:30:00,580
So, Anna,

954
01:30:01,480 --> 01:30:03,010
now we're going to play:

955
01:30:03,090 --> 01:30:05,520
"The Loving Wife", or...

956
01:30:05,590 --> 01:30:07,470
Whether by knife or whether by gun

957
01:30:07,470 --> 01:30:09,680
Losing your life can sometimes be fun.

958
01:30:13,030 --> 01:30:14,690
Hey! No falling asleep!

959
01:30:15,370 --> 01:30:18,560
You have to play with us,
or you'll be gagged again.

960
01:30:18,640 --> 01:30:20,470
That's not very nice, is it?

961
01:30:23,410 --> 01:30:26,570
So, here are the rules of the game:

962
01:30:26,650 --> 01:30:29,840
Georgie senior has been counted out,
so it's his turn.

963
01:30:31,180 --> 01:30:32,850
It'll be hard to change that.

964
01:30:33,690 --> 01:30:35,850
Unless you want to take his place.

965
01:30:37,020 --> 01:30:38,510
Do you want to?

966
01:30:41,060 --> 01:30:44,330
I'm sure Fatty will understand.
Right, Fatty?

967
01:30:44,400 --> 01:30:46,060
Don't call me Fatty.

968
01:30:46,130 --> 01:30:50,470
- You see, he understands.
- Get this over with. That's enough.

969
01:30:50,540 --> 01:30:52,200
That's enough?

970
01:30:52,270 --> 01:30:53,940
You think that's enough?

971
01:30:55,810 --> 01:30:57,470
What do you think, Anna?

972
01:30:57,580 --> 01:30:59,910
Have you had enough?
Or do you want to play some more?

973
01:31:00,720 --> 01:31:02,310
Don't reply anymore.

974
01:31:02,390 --> 01:31:04,720
Let them do what they want. Please!

975
01:31:04,790 --> 01:31:06,950
Then it'll be over quicker.

976
01:31:07,020 --> 01:31:09,190
Huh, that's cowardly!

977
01:31:09,260 --> 01:31:12,090
We're not up to feature film length yet.

978
01:31:12,160 --> 01:31:14,100
Is that enough?

979
01:31:14,170 --> 01:31:15,590
But you want a real ending,

980
01:31:15,590 --> 01:31:17,970
with plausible plot development, don't you?

981
01:31:18,040 --> 01:31:21,670
The bet is still on.
It can't be withdrawn unilaterally.

982
01:31:22,340 --> 01:31:23,430
So:

983
01:31:23,510 --> 01:31:25,910
the game is called: "The Loving Wife. "

984
01:31:25,980 --> 01:31:29,310
Although Beavis has done the counting,
she can choose...

985
01:31:29,380 --> 01:31:31,870
who will be next. And...

986
01:31:31,950 --> 01:31:33,610
using what implement!

987
01:31:34,290 --> 01:31:36,450
Do we prefer the little knife?

988
01:31:36,520 --> 01:31:38,360
Or the rifle?

989
01:31:39,590 --> 01:31:41,760
Well then, what does the housewife say?

990
01:31:46,270 --> 01:31:48,260
Hello, wakey, wakey!

991
01:31:50,970 --> 01:31:53,910
So, you're not interested?

992
01:31:53,980 --> 01:31:56,070
You don't want to play anymore.

993
01:31:57,180 --> 01:31:59,340
Beavis, show her the game again.

994
01:31:59,420 --> 01:32:00,610
Wait.

995
01:32:00,690 --> 01:32:02,020
Here you are.

996
01:32:02,090 --> 01:32:03,580
Hey, careful!

997
01:32:03,660 --> 01:32:05,320
I almost cut myself.

998
01:32:05,390 --> 01:32:06,880
Really?

999
01:32:17,940 --> 01:32:21,100
You see. It's the little knife.
You can spare him that.

1000
01:32:21,170 --> 01:32:23,010
You only have to play with us.

1001
01:32:26,110 --> 01:32:27,770
I understand, Anna.

1002
01:32:27,850 --> 01:32:29,340
I understand, really!

1003
01:32:30,350 --> 01:32:33,520
It's not a good feeling,
causing the one you love to suffer.

1004
01:32:35,190 --> 01:32:38,250
But it costs so little to avoid all that.

1005
01:32:38,330 --> 01:32:41,820
You only need follow the rules,
and all will be well.

1006
01:33:08,800 --> 01:33:09,890
What must I do?

1007
01:33:12,930 --> 01:33:15,090
You see, it wasn't that difficult.

1008
01:33:15,770 --> 01:33:17,530
And we'll make it easy too.

1009
01:33:17,610 --> 01:33:19,770
You recite a prayer of your choice.

1010
01:33:19,840 --> 01:33:22,340
If you say it flawlessly, God will help you

1011
01:33:22,340 --> 01:33:24,370
and you choose what happens next.

1012
01:33:30,220 --> 01:33:32,550
Or shall we carry on with Georgie senior?

1013
01:33:34,290 --> 01:33:35,320
I don't know a prayer.

1014
01:33:36,990 --> 01:33:38,650
You don't know any prayers?

1015
01:33:39,560 --> 01:33:41,460
Not a single prayer?

1016
01:33:43,900 --> 01:33:44,890
Is that possible?

1017
01:33:46,070 --> 01:33:47,560
Tell her one, Fatty.

1018
01:33:47,640 --> 01:33:49,660
Stop calling me Fatty all the time.

1019
01:33:49,740 --> 01:33:51,730
I'll stop saying it. Well?

1020
01:33:53,680 --> 01:33:56,150
Oh Lord and Father, make me kind,
So I, in heaven, my place may find.

1021
01:33:56,220 --> 01:33:59,240
- That's too easy.
- I can't think of any others.

1022
01:34:00,420 --> 01:34:01,580
Okay.

1023
01:34:01,650 --> 01:34:04,320
Oh Lord and Father, make me kind,
So I, in heaven, my place may find.

1024
01:34:06,330 --> 01:34:08,260
No! Not like that!

1025
01:34:08,330 --> 01:34:09,820
It's a prayer.

1026
01:34:09,900 --> 01:34:12,490
You can't just drone on like that.

1027
01:34:12,570 --> 01:34:15,730
You're asking the Lord God for something.
So pray properly.

1028
01:34:17,610 --> 01:34:20,080
Go on.
Go down on your knees properly.

1029
01:34:21,410 --> 01:34:23,500
Go on! Get on with it!

1030
01:34:28,850 --> 01:34:31,620
There. That's right. Kneel down properly.

1031
01:34:34,130 --> 01:34:36,060
Put your hands together.

1032
01:34:36,730 --> 01:34:38,560
Not on your stomach.

1033
01:34:38,630 --> 01:34:41,290
Where is the one you pray to?
Up there!

1034
01:34:42,200 --> 01:34:44,970
You have to pray to the heavens!
That's it!

1035
01:34:46,570 --> 01:34:50,240
Right, and now, in a fervent tone,
if you don't mind.

1036
01:34:56,450 --> 01:34:59,280
- Beavis, can you help her a little?
- No!

1037
01:35:07,930 --> 01:35:10,090
Oh Lord and Father, make me kind,

1038
01:35:12,600 --> 01:35:14,430
So I, in heaven, my place may find.

1039
01:35:14,500 --> 01:35:15,970
Well done!
You did that well!

1040
01:35:17,310 --> 01:35:20,800
That was the trial run,
and now we're going for Olympic Gold:

1041
01:35:20,880 --> 01:35:24,210
If you can recite this prayer,
which is sadly much too short,

1042
01:35:24,280 --> 01:35:26,940
from back to front, without any mistakes,

1043
01:35:27,020 --> 01:35:31,320
you can not only choose
which of you kicks the bucket first,

1044
01:35:31,390 --> 01:35:35,660
but also, and no doubt
this will interest you more - how.

1045
01:35:35,730 --> 01:35:39,990
whether quick and painless by the bullet...

1046
01:35:40,070 --> 01:35:41,530
Careful!

1047
01:35:48,010 --> 01:35:49,980
Where's the remote?

1048
01:35:51,180 --> 01:35:53,510
Where's the fucking remote control?

1049
01:36:19,780 --> 01:36:22,940
That was the trial run,
and now we're going for Olympic Gold:

1050
01:36:23,010 --> 01:36:26,850
If you can recite this prayer,
which is sadly much too short,

1051
01:36:26,920 --> 01:36:30,580
from back to front, without any mistakes,

1052
01:36:30,660 --> 01:36:33,650
you can not only choose
which of you kicks the bucket first,

1053
01:36:33,730 --> 01:36:38,060
but also, and no doubt
this will interest you more - how:

1054
01:36:38,130 --> 01:36:40,970
whether quick and painless by the bul -

1055
01:36:44,710 --> 01:36:48,540
You shouldn't have done that, Anna.
One doesn't break the rules.

1056
01:36:48,610 --> 01:36:51,440
Sorry. You've failed.

1057
01:36:54,820 --> 01:36:57,310
Say good-bye to Georgie.

1058
01:37:32,290 --> 01:37:34,280
Would you sit down?

1059
01:38:14,740 --> 01:38:16,230
Can you give me your gloves?

1060
01:38:21,380 --> 01:38:23,870
...only it's all inverted.

1061
01:38:23,950 --> 01:38:27,410
But of course all these predictions are wrong
so as to avoid a panic.

1062
01:38:27,490 --> 01:38:28,980
But now Kelvin knows how it really is...

1063
01:38:29,060 --> 01:38:32,220
and wants to warn his wife
and daughter in time.

1064
01:38:32,290 --> 01:38:34,110
But the problem is not only getting

1065
01:38:34,110 --> 01:38:36,290
from the world of antimatter to reality,

1066
01:38:36,370 --> 01:38:37,890
- but also to regain communication -
- Look!

1067
01:38:39,240 --> 01:38:40,930
Now that's a sporting attitude!

1068
01:38:45,140 --> 01:38:46,970
Hey, look out, fatso!

1069
01:38:47,040 --> 01:38:48,530
I thought you were a non-swimmer.

1070
01:38:56,890 --> 01:38:59,050
Go and get the widow.
She'll feel lonely otherwise.

1071
01:39:02,860 --> 01:39:04,520
Would you mind cooperating?

1072
01:39:04,600 --> 01:39:07,570
It's not easy.
Otherwise I might hurt you.

1073
01:39:13,070 --> 01:39:15,010
So. Where was I?

1074
01:39:15,080 --> 01:39:18,570
The communication problems
between matter and antimatter.

1075
01:39:18,650 --> 01:39:21,310
Exactly. As if you were in a black hole!

1076
01:39:21,380 --> 01:39:25,220
Gravitation is so strong that nothing
can escape it: absolute silence.

1077
01:39:25,290 --> 01:39:26,950
- By the way, what's the time?
- What?

1078
01:39:27,020 --> 01:39:28,510
What's the time?

1079
01:39:28,590 --> 01:39:30,080
Just after eight.

1080
01:39:30,160 --> 01:39:31,150
Already?

1081
01:39:38,140 --> 01:39:39,300
Why?

1082
01:39:39,370 --> 01:39:42,530
The deadline was at 9:00.
She had almost an hour left!

1083
01:39:42,610 --> 01:39:45,070
Firstly,
it was too hard to sail like that,

1084
01:39:45,140 --> 01:39:49,640
- and secondly, I'm starting to get hungry.
- That's true.

1085
01:40:03,000 --> 01:40:04,990
...when Kelvin overcomes gravitation,

1086
01:40:05,070 --> 01:40:07,400
it turns out that one universe is real,

1087
01:40:07,470 --> 01:40:09,630
but the other is just a fiction.

1088
01:40:09,700 --> 01:40:11,070
How does that happen?

1089
01:40:11,140 --> 01:40:14,470
What do I know! It was a kind of
model projection in cyberspace.

1090
01:40:14,540 --> 01:40:17,880
And where is your hero now?
In reality or fiction?

1091
01:40:17,950 --> 01:40:20,440
His family is in reality
and he's in fiction.

1092
01:40:20,520 --> 01:40:23,680
- But the fiction is real, isn't it?
- How do you mean?

1093
01:40:23,750 --> 01:40:26,750
- Well, you see it in the film, right?
- Of course.

1094
01:40:26,820 --> 01:40:30,120
So, it's just as real as the reality
which you see likewise, right?

1095
01:40:30,190 --> 01:40:31,320
- Crap.
- Why?

1096
01:40:59,890 --> 01:41:02,230
Is anyone awake yet?

1097
01:41:09,340 --> 01:41:10,830
Who is it?

1098
01:41:18,180 --> 01:41:19,340
Good morning to you.

1099
01:41:19,420 --> 01:41:21,910
Sorry to disturb you so early,
but I've come from Anna's.

1100
01:41:21,990 --> 01:41:23,480
And?

1101
01:41:24,820 --> 01:41:26,480
Don't you remember me?

1102
01:41:26,560 --> 01:41:29,220
Yesterday afternoon, on the jetty.
I'm Paul.

1103
01:41:29,290 --> 01:41:30,780
Oh, yes.

1104
01:41:32,000 --> 01:41:33,830
- Good morning.
- Morning.

1105
01:41:33,900 --> 01:41:37,230
Anna sent me. We had guests arrive
unexpectedly this morning...

1106
01:41:37,300 --> 01:41:40,300
and she wonders if
you could spare her a few eggs?

1107
01:41:40,370 --> 01:41:41,860
I think so.

1108
01:41:41,940 --> 01:41:43,430
Come in.

1109
01:41:43,510 --> 01:41:45,670
Wait a minute.

